Review system -> Boosters and posters review each other after a run to evaluate "how enjoyable doing key with that person was." It is an evaluation for recommending that person to others. So be chill in keys, be friendly, and try to do your best. Don't get angry, don't curse people, don't get toxic

Appeals -> You can ask others to vote for your review to get deleted. Other people have 3 days to check the appeal and vote on it anonymously. It's a community driven system. If people don't participate and vote, the appeals would not get enough votes and get rejected
Premium Appeals -> Same as appeals, but a guaranteed review by an admin in 24 hours

My suggestion is that don't stress at all if your overall review score is above 9 and don't freak out if it's above 8 (but try to improve it)
If you are below 8, then things gets hard for you to be picked
Don't freak out by 1 bad review and instead of blaming others, try to think what led you to get that review
Don't leave revenge reviews as it's promoting a toxic culture that will eventually happen to you too
Ask for your team to give you good reviews if you deserve it at the end of the run to improve your reviews and make them more resilient to bad ones (as when you do bad the chances are high that you get a bad review, but when you do good, people are less likely to leave you a review until you ask them to)
